Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.15,0:00:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to our program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.49,0:00:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a preview \Nof what we can look forward to.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.76,0:00:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This brother began \Nhis ministry in the Congo \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.19,0:00:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,when his fellow Witnesses \Nwere few in number. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.83,0:00:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jehovah bless his hard work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.23,0:00:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to preach and shepherd?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.57,0:00:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a joy when we come together \Nat Assembly Halls for spiritual programs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.37,0:00:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But how much work goes into caring \Nfor these places of pure worship?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.48,0:00:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We also work to maintain \Npeaceful relationships \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.31,0:00:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.32,0:00:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What lesson does this sister learn \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.95,0:00:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that lets her see \Nthe beautiful qualities in others?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.59,0:00:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’ll consider the privilege we have \Nto be fellow workers with God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.46,0:00:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re watching the October 2017 edition \Nof JW Broadcasting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.22,0:01:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with a report \Nfrom the United States branch \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.56,0:01:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in Wallkill, New York. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.56,0:01:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Any Bethel assignment is a joy \Nand sometimes a challenge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.56,0:01:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Proper training is therefore \Nan important part of every job. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.20,0:01:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the Maintenance Department \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.27,0:01:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,train hundreds of volunteers \Nto work efficiently and safely? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.28,0:01:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do the students feel \Nabout the practical training they receive?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.79,0:01:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,There were a few factors\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.69,0:01:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that created the need at Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.19,0:01:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,for a more structured training program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.83,0:01:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,One of those factors included\Nthe regular changeover in personnel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.83,0:01:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers have to be more versatile\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.53,0:01:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in their assignments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.54,0:02:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They may have to do tasks they\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,previously weren’t trained on.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.67,0:02:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Printing equipment became\Nmore technologically advanced; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.21,0:02:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,our building systems\Nbecame more complicated; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.25,0:02:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,computer systems were now starting\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.25,0:02:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to be used to control virtually everything.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.58,0:02:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I feel like Bethel has definitely\Nalways been good about training,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.92,0:02:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but especially now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.96,0:02:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I think everyone sees \Nthe need to continue investing\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.66,0:02:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the brothers and sisters\Nthat are currently at Bethel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.06,0:02:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think it’s possible for someone\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.57,0:02:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to know less about the trades \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.37,0:02:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,than I did when I started.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.60,0:02:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember my first reaction\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.24,0:02:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was invited to help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.74,0:02:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in electrical was fear.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.11,0:02:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I received my assignment,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.24,0:02:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out that it involved\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.71,0:02:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,running the heavy equipment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.88,0:02:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So I called my parents. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.22,0:02:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really excited about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.22,0:02:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “Mom and Dad,\Nguess what I get to do?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.42,0:02:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And Dad said, “OK, Son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.75,0:02:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, did you tell them\Nthat you don’t know how to drive?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.29,0:02:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It was decided to pull a group\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.49,0:03:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of highly experienced, \Nhighly skilled brothers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.66,0:03:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to concentrate \Non developing and teaching\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.13,0:03:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,repeatable, consistent classes\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.74,0:03:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that could bring people’s skill levels\Nup to what was needed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.28,0:03:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We teach well over 100 different classes\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.14,0:03:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in 12 major categories.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.61,0:03:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Here at Bethel, \NI’ve probably been\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.48,0:03:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a part of over 30 different classes,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.92,0:03:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so it’s been a variety, \Ndepending on\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.69,0:03:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the needs at the time \Nof the assignment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.52,0:03:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I would estimate \Nthat I’ve taken about 15\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.83,0:03:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,or 20 different courses\Nfrom safety and training \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.39,0:03:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,over the course of my 13 years \Nin learning a trade. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.96,0:03:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve become certified\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.43,0:03:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in at least these\Nseven different licensed requirements.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.00,0:03:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We teach people technical skills, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.44,0:03:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but that’s not the sole purpose \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.01,0:03:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of the training.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.07,0:03:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you aren’t skilled in safety, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.37,0:03:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you can’t be skilled\Nin your trade and vice versa.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.84,0:03:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The objective in all of our safety courses\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.81,0:03:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is to get them to view safety\Nthe same way Jehovah views it\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.68,0:03:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,—as a reflection of their spirituality.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.02,0:03:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So training in safety is essential.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.46,0:04:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So our goal is to take them\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.79,0:04:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,into the classroom\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.86,0:04:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and give them some time\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.96,0:04:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to consider the theoretical. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.53,0:04:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we take them out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.66,0:04:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,where there is a lab set up, \Nand we have them do some tests on it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.33,0:04:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Typically, they will tell us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.33,0:04:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that they’ve been able to learn \Nmore in a week \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.70,0:04:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,than what they have learned\Nin a year of trade school.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.34,0:04:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve done over 60,000 instances of training.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.48,0:04:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so now receiving this training, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.48,0:04:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it provides an area or an aspect\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.18,0:04:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in which I can give \Nmy 100 percent to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.65,0:04:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it in their eyes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.22,0:04:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re just so happy\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.65,0:04:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that they now have maybe a new skill \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.72,0:04:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,or a new understanding\Nthat they can use to benefit Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I love the fact that I came\Ninto Bethel with virtually no experience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.73,0:04:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And not only did I \Nreceive a trade that I could use\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.50,0:04:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to carry out a work \Nthat glorifies Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.04,0:04:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but I was trained well enough\Nthat I can share that with others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and they can be trained too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.78,0:04:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Helping someone else \Nto go from that feeling \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.51,0:05:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of not knowing anything \Nto feeling productive\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.68,0:05:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and feeling like they’re \Ncontributing is a real joy for me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.72,0:05:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can take what they learn\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.49,0:05:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,wherever they go.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.92,0:05:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The confidence that people\Nleave with once they’ve received \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.73,0:05:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that investment\N—it’s confidence that they can carry out\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.63,0:05:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever assignment\NJehovah has given them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.73,0:05:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the confidence that Jehovah\Nis going to train them\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for whatever is being asked of them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.30,0:05:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I think if younger brothers and sisters\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,are trying to learn a skill\Nso that they can come to Bethel,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.11,0:05:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s commendable, \Nbut more important is spirituality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Let Jehovah “finish your training.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.05,0:05:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In regard to training,\Nwe’re really only getting started.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.62,0:05:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The training that we are getting \Nin this system of things by Jehovah,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.86,0:05:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially related to safety, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is absolutely going\Nto be vital in the new world.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.76,0:05:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can imagine the idea\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of being able to use\Nsome of the things I’ve learned\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.43,0:05:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to figure out how \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.30,0:05:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we can use the natural resources\Nin a way without using them up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.00,0:05:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that we serve a God \Nwho is known as the “Grand Instructor.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.74,0:05:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the things that we’re\Nteaching and training right now,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.81,0:06:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it can only expand in the future.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.68,0:06:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And as long as you let him train you,\Nyou’re going to be all right.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.72,0:06:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good training gives us confidence \Nto do our best for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.09,0:06:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s true at Bethel \Nbut also true in the field.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.13,0:06:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you, though, \Never felt alone in your assignment,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,even if for just a few hours\Nin the ministry? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.57,0:06:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Pontien Mukanga may have felt\Nthat way early in his assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the first circuit overseer\Nfor all of what is now\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.48,0:06:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the Democratic Republic of Congo\Nand the Republic of Congo. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.68,0:06:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He traveled great distances to visit\Nthe few brothers throughout the territory. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.32,0:06:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to what encouraged him\Nthe most to keep going.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.53,0:06:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1960,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.53,0:06:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was made a circuit overseer\Nfor the whole of Congo. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.97,0:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so happy to receive this privilege. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.47,0:07:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was shocked and scared. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.41,0:07:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The assignment was huge.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.58,0:07:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Congo is a vast country. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.58,0:07:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid to go to places I didn’t know. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.09,0:07:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt overwhelmed, \Nso I turned to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.73,0:07:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I had to go through\Nsavannahs and across the jungle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.20,0:07:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There were wild animals. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.83,0:07:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, I climbed up a tree\Nto find a place to sleep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I tied myself to a branch with my belt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.37,0:07:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid I would be taken by a boa snake.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.28,0:07:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid of getting lost in the forest.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.68,0:07:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Visiting the brothers was very difficult. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.75,0:07:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes the journey took many days. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember one day, \NI left my house\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.93,0:07:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to visit the brothers to encourage them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I left at 5:30 in the morning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.13,0:08:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I arrived at 7:30 that night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.17,0:08:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to push my bicycle through sand\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.74,0:08:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for up to 13 miles (21 km) or even more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.24,0:08:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Other times, we traveled by truck. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.65,0:08:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That was not easy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.65,0:08:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You had to climb on top of the truck. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.05,0:08:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to hold on tight so as not to fall.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.72,0:08:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Congregations, isolated groups\Nwere far away from one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.46,0:08:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There were no phones at that time either. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though they did not know I was coming,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.57,0:08:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they made me feel so welcome. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.41,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers were really very hospitable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When I arrived, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.91,0:08:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was exhausted\Nbut so happy to see the brothers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.35,0:09:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kitawala was a religion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.16,0:09:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent many letters\Nto the Belgium branch\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.59,0:09:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,asking to be recognized\Nas Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.47,0:09:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,These people used\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.83,0:09:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our publications\Nand used the name Watch Tower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.24,0:09:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It created a lot of confusion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.48,0:09:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,To clarify the matter,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.65,0:09:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the organization prepared a booklet.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.45,0:09:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My mission was to check whether\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.55,0:09:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there were any genuine\NJehovah’s Witnesses in Kisangani. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.86,0:09:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We found out that these people were\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.06,0:09:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In all the confusion, \Npeople even tried to kill me\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,during the trip. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.17,0:09:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Fortunately, I managed to escape. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.08,0:09:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it was Jehovah\Nwho assigned me this privilege,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.92,0:10:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was confident\Nthat he would always help me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.26,0:10:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, I am very happy\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.76,0:10:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to have at my side my children, \Nmy grandchildren,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.43,0:10:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and my great-grandchildren\N—all Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.97,0:10:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has given me many blessings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.91,0:10:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I am truly grateful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.71,0:10:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What a joy to be used by Almighty God.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.91,0:10:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Through all these years,\NI have never lacked anything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.05,0:10:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has given me the strength \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.05,0:10:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve him up until now—to the age of 86. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.99,0:10:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In everything and for everything, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.20,0:10:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,my trust really is in Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.23,0:10:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There were 46 publishers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.27,0:10:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in the whole of Congo. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.60,0:10:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I hear there are more than\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.11,0:11:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,223,000 Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.44,0:11:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Congo.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.61,0:11:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, when I see\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.32,0:11:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the increase of Jehovah’s people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.02,0:11:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to me it is like a miracle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.30,0:11:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I thank Jehovah \Nfor allowing me to see \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.07,0:11:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,‘the little one become a thousand’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.07,0:11:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,here in the Congo.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.81,0:11:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Mukanga continues to serve\Nas an elder at nearly 88 years old. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.29,0:11:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine yourself\Nexperiencing both the joys\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.42,0:11:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and difficulties he had\Nas a circuit overseer? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.73,0:11:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He courageously visited\Nthe Kitawala religious groups\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.33,0:11:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who claimed to serve Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.57,0:12:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,only to find some were violent\Nand practiced immorality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.20,0:12:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was his reliance on Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and watching Him turn\Nthe small group of brothers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.11,0:12:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,into more than 200,000\Nthat has kept him going.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.18,0:12:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He personally experienced \Nour theme for this program: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“The Privilege and Blessing \Nof Being God’s Fellow Worker.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jehovah’s people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.63,0:12:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we enjoy many undeserved\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.63,0:12:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and precious privileges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.63,0:12:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Among them, we bear Jehovah’s name\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.07,0:12:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and render him sacred service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.77,0:12:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As we carry out his will, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.24,0:12:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,he dignifies us in a very special way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.48,0:12:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At 1 Corinthians 3:9,\Nthe apostle Paul under inspiration\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.22,0:12:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,stated that “we are God’s fellow workers.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.89,0:12:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What an honor to be a fellow worker\Nwith the Universal Sovereign,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.66,0:12:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,our loving heavenly Father! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.66,0:13:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To build appreciation for the privilege\Nof working with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.20,0:13:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re going to review events\Nin the life of Jonathan, a son of King Saul. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.44,0:13:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:45 \Ndescribes Jonathan when it says:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.74,0:13:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For it was with God\Nthat he acted this day.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.15,0:13:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the background\Nthat led to this statement? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.88,0:13:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Jonathan act, or work,\Nwith Jehovah on that day? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.92,0:13:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What lessons can we learn\Nfrom their working relationship? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.23,0:13:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And what blessings result\Nfrom being a fellow worker with God?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.43,0:13:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us begin with some background. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 12:20 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.01,0:13:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,records the encouraging words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.11,0:13:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,spoken by the prophet Samuel \Nto the nation of Israel: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.64,0:13:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not be afraid.  . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.75,0:13:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“Only do not turn away\Nfrom following Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.12,0:13:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and serve Jehovah \Nwith all your heart.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.99,0:13:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 22 adds:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.12,0:14:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the sake of his great name, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.82,0:14:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will not abandon his people.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.19,0:14:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as they remained faithful, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would always be there to guide,\Nprotect, and rescue them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.57,0:14:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,These words no doubt strengthened\NJonathan to carry out Jehovah’s directive\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.61,0:14:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to subdue the enemy nations\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.78,0:14:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and take possession of the Promised Land.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.65,0:14:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,At  1 Samuel chapter 13, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we read that Jonathan \Nwas assigned 1,000 men\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.85,0:14:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to attack a Philistine garrison at Geba. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.76,0:14:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Although poorly equipped,\NJonathan and his men succeeded. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.93,0:14:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This victory strengthened \NJonathan’s confidence in Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and provides a valuable lesson for us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.40,0:14:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,While we gain strength and courage\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah’s reassuring\Nwords of the Scriptures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.44,0:14:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,our confidence in Jehovah’s support\Nbecomes even stronger\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.51,0:14:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,when we successfully\Ncarry out our assignments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.55,0:15:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that may seem overwhelming.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The account then relates\Nhow the Philistines\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.59,0:15:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,were infuriated over their defeat\Nand mounted a massive counterattack. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.03,0:15:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent out raiding parties \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.03,0:15:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,from their camp \Nat Michmash near Jerusalem. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.43,0:15:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Many Israelite men hid out of fear, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.73,0:15:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and some even fled\Nto the other side of the Jordan River.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.37,0:15:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In contrast,\NJonathan remained courageous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.28,0:15:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Determined to put a stop to the raids, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.81,0:15:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,he confronted the Philistine outpost\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.31,0:15:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at the ravine pass of Michmash. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.88,0:15:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The approach was by way of a deep gorge\Nwith nearly vertical cliffs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.36,0:15:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This would have seemed next to impossible\Nto someone unfamiliar with the area, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.30,0:15:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jonathan grew up in this territory\Nand apparently knew it well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.50,0:15:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,His knowledge of the surroundings\Nprovides another practical lesson:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.44,0:16:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever theocratic assignment\Nwe may be given,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.48,0:16:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,putting forth time and effort \Nto get to know the terrain, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.38,0:16:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so to speak,\Nwill contribute to our effectiveness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.28,0:16:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When we show interest\Nin our assigned work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.79,0:16:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we become even more effective\Nfellow workers of Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.69,0:16:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read as Jonathan prepares\Nto take action against the Philistines. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.46,0:16:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:6 states:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.10,0:16:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Jonathan said to his armor-bearer:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.80,0:16:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Come and let us cross over \Nto the outpost of these uncircumcised men. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.64,0:16:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Perhaps Jehovah will act in our behalf, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.64,0:16:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for nothing can hinder Jehovah\Nfrom saving by many or by few.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.42,0:16:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What contributed\Nto his confidence in Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.19,0:16:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Recall that he put faith\Nin Jehovah’s reassuring words\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.56,0:16:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,through the prophet Samuel: \N“Do not be afraid. . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.49,0:16:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of his great name,\NJehovah will not abandon his people.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.77,0:16:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He experienced Jehovah’s support \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.84,0:17:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when he struck down\Nthe Philistine garrison at Geba. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.27,0:17:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan could also\Nthink back on Israel’s history. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.24,0:17:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He could reflect\Non how Gideon and his 300 men\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.28,0:17:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,were victorious over 135,000 Midianites. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.69,0:17:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He could meditate\Non Samson killing 1,000 Philistines\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.82,0:17:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the jawbone of a donkey. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.56,0:17:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Such examples \Nwould bolster his confidence\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.56,0:17:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was working \Nwith the Almighty God, Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.14,0:17:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We too can meditate on fellow workers\Nof God recorded in the Scriptures\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.44,0:17:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as published life stories\Nof modern-day faithful servants. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.75,0:17:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Such examples\Nreinforce our faith in Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.88,0:17:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as we rely on him for success.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.42,0:17:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Another lesson comes from the response\Nof Jonathan’s armor-bearer\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.02,0:17:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Samuel 14:7: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.89,0:17:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“At this his armor-bearer said to him:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.73,0:18:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do whatever your heart impels you to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.93,0:18:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Turn wherever you wish, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.17,0:18:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will follow you \Nwherever your heart impels you.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.54,0:18:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It is unlikely that the attendant\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.74,0:18:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,would have initiated\Nthis challenging mission on his own. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.78,0:18:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan’s confident lead was a positive, \Nmotivating influence on the man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens today\Nwhen elders and overseers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.05,0:18:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,take the lead and display zeal\Nin Jehovah’s work like Jonathan? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.69,0:18:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Others in the congregation are also\Nmotivated to action by their fine example.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.57,0:18:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us now read verses 8-10:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.47,0:18:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Jonathan said:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.94,0:18:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘We will cross over to those men\Nand reveal our presence to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.61,0:18:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘If they say to us,\N“Stand still until we come to you!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.98,0:18:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘we will stand where we are\Nand not go up to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.22,0:18:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘But if they say, “Come up against us!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.79,0:19:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘we will go up, because Jehovah \Nwill give them into our hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.56,0:19:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be our sign.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan once again demonstrated\Nhumble reliance on Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.17,0:19:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Later in Second Samuel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.17,0:19:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan is described\Nas “swifter than the eagles”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.37,0:19:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and “mightier than the lions.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.34,0:19:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However, these qualities\Nand abilities did not cause him\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.38,0:19:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to be self-reliant or overconfident. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.42,0:19:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He sought Jehovah’s direction\Nby means of a sign. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.59,0:19:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful reminder for us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.36,0:19:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless of any natural abilities,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.26,0:19:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,acquired skills,\Nor experience we may have,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.56,0:19:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the key to success is seeking\NJehovah’s guidance and support. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.97,0:19:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We seek his direction\Nthrough specific prayers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.37,0:19:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible reading and meditation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.98,0:19:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and applying direction\Nfrom “the faithful and discreet slave.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.15,0:20:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We also consult \Nwith longtime faithful brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.42,0:20:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who can share their rich experience\Nas God’s fellow workers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.39,0:20:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,One such example was Sister Joey Orrom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,who served in the Britain branch. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.73,0:20:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She shared her experiences \Nin an archived interview \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.73,0:20:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,some time before finishing \Nher earthly course in 2011. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen also to the comments \Nof her fellow workers in Britain \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.01,0:20:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who benefited from their time together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.42,0:20:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the privilege for two years\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.42,0:20:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of sitting at the same table\Nas Sister Orrom for morning worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.32,0:20:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She expected nothing and appreciated\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.96,0:20:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that you did for her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.59,0:20:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Orrom\Nwas affectionately known as Joey. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.10,0:20:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you take the “e” out of Joey, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.43,0:20:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re left with the English word “joy,”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.64,0:20:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and that summed her up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.30,0:20:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,My impression of Joey\Nwhen I first met her\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.84,0:21:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was here is this frail old lady. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.44,0:21:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But then when you\Nstarted to speak to Joey, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.38,0:21:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you were tapping\Ninto a tremendous depth.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.62,0:21:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,About the age of 20, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.22,0:21:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,round about that time,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.38,0:21:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the heavenly calling. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.02,0:21:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a big battle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.55,0:21:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t understand why Jehovah\Nwould use a person like me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.59,0:21:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And when I was 21,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.16,0:21:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I got into pioneering, in 1939. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.86,0:21:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But the police were after me\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.93,0:21:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because I wouldn’t join the armed forces,\Nand I was tried under a new act. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.74,0:21:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And they kept taking me\Ninto a side room and saying,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you will say you are not connected\Nwith Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.94,0:21:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,not connected with the Watch Tower,\Nyou’ll have a walk away.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.14,0:21:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I said: “I am connected\Nwith the Watch Tower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.55,0:21:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m proud to be connected\Nwith the Watch Tower.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.75,0:21:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And they said,\N“Then they are directing you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.15,0:21:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “No, my stand of not doing\Nas you wish is my own personal stand.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.06,0:21:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So this went on. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.16,0:21:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, they sent me\Nto prison just for two months \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.89,0:21:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and then let me out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.23,0:21:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I partnered with another sister, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.23,0:21:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and she and I went to Northern Ireland \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.84,0:22:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and pioneered there for 18 months. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.57,0:22:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was in Northern Ireland\Nthat we had our call to Gilead.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.84,0:22:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1948, Joey was invited to Gilead, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.54,0:22:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was the 11th class.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.91,0:22:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It left an impression on me, \Nwhich I will never ever, ever forget. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.68,0:22:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You pick up that spirit \Nof good behavior, of love. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.18,0:22:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s something that leaves\Nits mark, or it should. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.79,0:22:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It has left its mark on me\N—very, very much so. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.16,0:22:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing Brother Knorr impressed on us:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.63,0:22:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“You’ll be three years on your assignment\Nbefore you really love it.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.86,0:22:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was true \Nbecause it was a hard assignment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.53,0:22:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,After Gilead, \Nshe was assigned to be a missionary\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.07,0:22:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in Dublin,\Nin the Irish Republic. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.07,0:22:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the time when Catholic priests\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.81,0:22:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,used to organize mobs against the pioneers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.88,0:22:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,She was full of joy, \Nbut that didn’t mean to say\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.91,0:22:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that she’d had an easy life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.62,0:22:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We never went out from door to door\Nwithout being mobbed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.15,0:22:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and attacked and beaten up\Nand thrown around. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.32,0:22:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And you could only do\Na few houses in a row, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.96,0:22:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’d have to get away very quickly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.03,0:22:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But we made a very good name. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.76,0:23:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,People got to know\Nwe were completely neutral.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.06,0:23:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They chose four of us\Nto work the business property, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.73,0:23:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got some studies\Ngoing in their offices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.97,0:23:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But one place I went into,\NI walked the length of this draper shop,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.97,0:23:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and I asked if I could go\Ninto the manager’s office. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.01,0:23:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As I went in, I didn’t say a word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.68,0:23:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t open my mouth\Nand even say good morning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.15,0:23:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but this man stood up,\Nand he said, “Russellite!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.18,0:23:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And he took hold of me\Nby the scruff of my neck\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.19,0:23:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and the seat of my pants,\Nand he lifted me up\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.66,0:23:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and he carried me\Nthe length of the store. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.63,0:23:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like a silly one,\NI should’ve gone heavy on him, you see. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.16,0:23:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead of that, \NI let my legs paddle\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.30,0:23:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was hanging onto my book bag,\Nnot wanting to lose it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.30,0:23:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And when he got \Nto the front door, the staff, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.94,0:23:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,their eyes were absolutely aghast\Nat what was happening. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.51,0:23:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He opened his front door\Nand threw me out, literally. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.21,0:23:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I went zoom!\Njust managed to go zoom! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.05,0:23:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the brothers was passing,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.22,0:23:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and he caught me\N—caught me steady—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.82,0:23:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and said, \N“Whatever is going on?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.22,0:24:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I couldn’t stop laughing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.22,0:24:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To me it was very, very funny. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.22,0:24:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest were so cross about it,\Nbut I wasn’t at all cross. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.66,0:24:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was quite hilarious. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.16,0:24:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see myself being carried\Nthrough this shop sky-high. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.70,0:24:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Things like that happened.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.47,0:24:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,These experiences \Ndid not dampen her zeal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.27,0:24:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She always retained that missionary spirit.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.31,0:24:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I first met Joey\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.04,0:24:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was commuting to Bethel\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.48,0:24:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in the infirmary.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.04,0:24:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She was sitting on that old-fashioned chair\Nwith this huge Bible,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.68,0:24:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and she stayed there hours reading the Bible,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.65,0:24:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,praying to Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.85,0:24:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Often, when you came in, \Nshe’d be in the middle of Bible reading. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.76,0:24:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And she’d be saying something like,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.39,0:24:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Daniel has just been thrown\Ninto the lion’s den!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.59,0:24:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or “Oh, Jehovah is really angry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.60,0:24:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s thundering from the heavens!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.40,0:24:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And it made me think, ‘Wow! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.60,0:24:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,‘She must have read\Nthe Bible so many times,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.70,0:24:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but every time it was as if it was\Nhappening right in front of her.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.80,0:24:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Right up until she became incapacitated,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.04,0:24:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,she was conducting Bible studies\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.24,0:24:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and helping people\Nto come to know Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.91,0:25:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She was looking forward\Nto her heavenly reward. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.05,0:25:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And for her that was the culmination\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.55,0:25:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of a life of joy in Jehovah’s service\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.79,0:25:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and that she was just transferring\Nto her next assignment.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.36,0:25:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m very, very grateful for work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.23,0:25:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, often in my prayers,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.13,0:25:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll pray to Jehovah that I’ll have\Nsome good work to do today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.00,0:25:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m very grateful to have work to do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.24,0:25:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Similar to what we \Nlearned about Jonathan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.01,0:25:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sister Orrom demonstrated \Nhumble reliance on Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.78,0:25:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So sure was her trust in God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.38,0:25:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that she could face even fearful situations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.02,0:25:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with a sense of humor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.39,0:25:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We may not be able to laugh \Nwhen enduring persecution, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.89,0:25:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can imitate Joey’s faith \Nand firm resolve.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.30,0:25:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What else can we learn\Nfrom Jonathan’s account? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.67,0:25:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Picking up at 1 Samuel 14:12, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.81,0:26:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan and his armor-bearer\Nadvance toward the Philistines. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.21,0:26:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,From their elevated location,\Nthe Philistines shout to them: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.52,0:26:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Come up to us,\Nand we will teach you a lesson!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.45,0:26:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“At once Jonathan said to his armor-bearer:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.86,0:26:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Follow me, for Jehovah will give them\Ninto the hand of Israel.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.46,0:26:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan had requested a specific sign,\Nand he got it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.70,0:26:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But it meant advancing \Nup a steep and treacherous incline \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.01,0:26:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,right into enemy hands. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.14,0:26:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone lacking complete trust \Nin Jehovah might have said,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.75,0:26:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“Before proceeding,\Nperhaps we should ask for another sign,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.58,0:26:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but not Jonathan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.02,0:26:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Without hesitation,\Nhe told his attendant to follow him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.59,0:26:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jehovah would give\Nthe enemy into their hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.83,0:26:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When we receive Jehovah’s direction, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.13,0:26:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,we should without hesitation\Nput our hearts into the work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.93,0:27:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,confident of Jehovah’s backing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.64,0:27:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened next? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.64,0:27:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:13, 14 reports:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.48,0:27:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“And Jonathan climbed up\Non his hands and feet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.75,0:27:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“and his armor-bearer was behind him;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.68,0:27:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the Philistines began\Nto fall before Jonathan,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.09,0:27:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“and his armor-bearer was putting \Nthem to death behind him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.56,0:27:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“In the first attack that Jonathan\Nand his armor-bearer made,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.36,0:27:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they struck down about 20 men.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.90,0:27:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Even after receiving\Na clear sign from Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.90,0:27:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it took great effort. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.90,0:27:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They had to ‘climb up\Non their hands and feet,’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.34,0:27:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,exerting themselves\Nvigorously over rugged terrain. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.88,0:27:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The lesson? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.91,0:27:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when we receive clear direction\Nand are ready to obey, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.52,0:27:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,carrying out our assignments\Nwill not always be easy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.02,0:27:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to exert ourselves vigorously, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.49,0:28:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,being willing to work hard \Nwith all of our mind, heart, and strength.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.10,0:28:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How did the Philistines react to seeing\NJehovah’s support for his people? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.00,0:28:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:15 reads:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.44,0:28:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then terror spread in the field camp \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.74,0:28:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“and among all the people of the outpost, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.31,0:28:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“and even the raiding parties were terrified. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.58,0:28:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The earth began quaking, \Nand a terror from God ensued.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.12,0:28:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The earthquake Jehovah caused\Nmelted the Philistines’ hearts. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.39,0:28:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, the Israelites, even those \Nwho had previously fled in fear,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.83,0:28:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,joined the victory battle\Nover the Philistines. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.10,0:28:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, when we put our hearts \Ninto theocratic assignments,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.44,0:28:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, our best Fellow Worker,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.14,0:28:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will always come through with whatever\Nwe need to accomplish his will.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.18,0:28:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is another lesson to be learned\Nfrom this exciting Bible account. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.89,0:28:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,During the height of the battle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.89,0:29:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,King Saul gave an unwise order saying:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.16,0:29:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“Cursed is the man who eats\Nany food before the evening\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.80,0:29:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and until I have taken \Nvengeance on my enemies!” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.30,0:29:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan, however, was not aware\Nof his father’s order\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.24,0:29:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and ate some wild honey \Nthat he had found.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.37,0:29:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Saul react when he discovered\Nthat his own son had disobeyed him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.91,0:29:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:43, 44 tells us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.52,0:29:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then Saul said to Jonathan:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.42,0:29:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Tell me, what have you done?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.22,0:29:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“So Jonathan told him:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.76,0:29:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I merely tasted a little honey\Non the tip of the staff in my hand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.07,0:29:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“Here I am! \NI am ready to die!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.57,0:29:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“At this Saul said:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.77,0:29:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Thus may God do and may he add to it\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.97,0:29:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if you do not die, Jonathan.’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.04,0:29:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine, after all that Jonathan had done\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.51,0:30:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in risking his life in behalf of his people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.52,0:30:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and seeing Jehovah grant so much success, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.72,0:30:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he is now being condemned\Nto death by his own father. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.13,0:30:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How his heart must have sank in disbelief, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.80,0:30:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,disappointment, and sadness!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.53,0:30:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Would Jehovah now abandon \Nhis loyal fellow worker? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.20,0:30:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,First Samuel 14:45 reads:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.81,0:30:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the people said to Saul: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.81,0:30:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Should Jonathan die\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.01,0:30:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘—the one who brought\Nthis great victory to Israel? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.95,0:30:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘It is unthinkable! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.95,0:30:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘As surely as Jehovah is alive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.45,0:30:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘not even a single hair of his head\Nshould fall to the ground, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.69,0:30:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“for it was with God that he acted this day.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.60,0:30:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With that the people rescued Jonathan,\Nand he did not die.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.07,0:30:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonathan’s success\Nprovided undeniable evidence\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.87,0:30:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was truly Jehovah’s fellow worker. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.58,0:31:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, who had been\Nat Jonathan’s side the whole time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.48,0:31:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,saw everything that had happened\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.88,0:31:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and would not allow his loyal worker\Nto die at Saul’s hands.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.65,0:31:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How comforting to know that when we\Nfaithfully carry out our assignments,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.93,0:31:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,he will never forget our zealous efforts! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.80,0:31:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If someone as close as a father\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.13,0:31:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,fails to see and appreciate \Nthe work we do in Jehovah’s service\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.00,0:31:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or even turns against us,\NJehovah will never forget our work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.71,0:31:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He will always be there to guide, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.18,0:31:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,support, protect, and bless us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.01,0:31:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What a faith-building account \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.02,0:31:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve considered \Nin 1 Samuel chapters 13 and 14! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.49,0:31:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not take the time\Nto read these chapters for yourself? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.56,0:31:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be moved to imitate\NJonathan’s excellent example of loyalty,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.70,0:31:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,courage, and obedience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.57,0:32:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to be described \Njust as Jonathan was at 1 Samuel 14:45:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.57,0:32:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“For it was with God\Nthat he acted this day.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.34,0:32:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,By continuing \Nas industrious fellow workers with Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.85,0:32:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we are assured\Nthat ‘through faith and patience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.95,0:32:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we will inherit the promised reward.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.42,0:32:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s look at another example \Nof modern-day fellow workers with God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.66,0:32:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Assembly Hall servants \Ncare for the cleaning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.16,0:32:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and maintenance \Nof these places of worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.17,0:32:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but they don’t do this work alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.20,0:32:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In this report from the United States, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.34,0:32:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll see how the work is organized, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.04,0:32:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll hear how \Nour brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.44,0:32:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,feel about being able \Nto help with the work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.98,0:32:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Assembly Hall is an educational center. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.59,0:32:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a center of pure worship \Nfor all the congregations that come. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.39,0:32:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Taking care of Jehovah’s house \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.19,0:33:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of sacred service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.06,0:33:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Even going back to the temple, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.83,0:33:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,everyone had an assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.83,0:33:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They had someone to open the doors. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.94,0:33:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, of course, they also had \Nsomebody maintaining things.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.31,0:33:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,As of December 2016, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.01,0:33:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,there are 773 Assembly Halls worldwide. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.75,0:33:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There are so many details \Nat an Assembly Hall; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.92,0:33:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you can’t do it all yourself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.79,0:33:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To be overseer of an Assembly Hall— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.52,0:33:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We were excited to do it, \Nbut it seemed real heavy at the time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.06,0:33:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It does take, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.73,0:33:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,in our particular case, a couple of hundred. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.93,0:33:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There are about 200 or so volunteers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.60,0:33:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,each and every week \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.14,0:33:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,that really are necessary \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.77,0:33:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to care for the Assembly Hall\N—the grounds, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.28,0:33:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the accounting, the purchasing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.85,0:33:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the maintenance,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.61,0:33:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and the cleaning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.28,0:33:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Each and every one of these chairs\N—the seating—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.29,0:34:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all have moving parts \Nand have to be maintained. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.79,0:34:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And with 4,050 seats in here, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.26,0:34:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we can say that every single one \Nof them has been maintained.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.23,0:34:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,John 2:17 says: \N“The zeal for your house will consume me.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.44,0:34:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think we have \Nan opportunity to show Jehovah that\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.74,0:34:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,—that we have zeal, \Nwe have an eagerness, a fire for his house, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.21,0:34:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and for caring for it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.58,0:34:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we appreciate all those \Nwho want to work at the Assembly Hall.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.49,0:34:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of the dear friends, \Nafter they just spent a whole day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.65,0:34:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,doing some terribly dirty job, \Nthey thank you for the privilege. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.16,0:34:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s zeal for Jehovah’s house. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.80,0:34:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowhere else does that happen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.80,0:34:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we tried to do it ourselves \Nor if we hired somebody, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.47,0:34:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it wouldn’t be as good as the work \Nthat the friends do when they come in.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.34,0:34:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When the friends come on the weekend, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.44,0:34:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this is an educational facility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.44,0:34:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So they come here \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.44,0:34:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to be educated about Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.65,0:34:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And new ones come, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.78,0:35:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and it needs to be dignified \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.88,0:35:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and reflect Jehovah’s qualities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.52,0:35:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So the cleaning that goes on \Nand the maintenance that goes on\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.62,0:35:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s what the purpose is.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.20,0:35:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,At lunchtime, we do a spiritual program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.57,0:35:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be a talk; \Nit could be a discussion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.30,0:35:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And we, really, \Ngenerally try to cover a topic \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.24,0:35:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that helps the volunteers \Nsee the connection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.71,0:35:30.78,Default,,0,0,0,,between their work \Nat the Assembly Hall \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.78,0:35:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Kingdom preaching work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.11,0:35:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We are preachers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.08,0:35:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s number one\N—to spread the good news. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.32,0:35:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see the results of that here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.32,0:35:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re filling this place up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.53,0:35:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a real privilege. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.53,0:35:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You learn so much \Nfrom the sacrifices that the friends make \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.91,0:36:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to serve Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.37,0:36:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that it makes us feel very small, \Nand we realize \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.85,0:36:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,what a blessing it is for us to be \Nin that environment all the time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.35,0:36:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal of any work in Jehovah’s service \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.45,0:36:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is to help as many people as you can \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.59,0:36:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to come to know him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.59,0:36:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and to take care of his interests\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.86,0:36:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,here on the earth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.86,0:36:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all have the same goal\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.59,0:36:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—trying to please him \Nand doing what we can.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.30,0:36:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal, really, as Assembly Hall servants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.54,0:36:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is to take care of the place in such a way\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.14,0:36:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—take care of the Assembly Hall \Nin such a way—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.25,0:36:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that not only saves and makes wise use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.65,0:36:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,of dedicated funds and resources \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.45,0:36:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,but also makes things ready \Nin such a way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.35,0:36:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that on Saturday morning \Nwhen the brothers and sisters walk in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.99,0:36:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and the attendants and the sound \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.09,0:36:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and the stage brothers are getting ready, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.23,0:36:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,all they really have to do \Nis come on in and flip the switches\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.73,0:36:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—lights come on, air conditioning, heat. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.23,0:37:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is functioning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.77,0:37:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All they have to do \Nis just focus on the program \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.64,0:37:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and listen and take in instruction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.41,0:37:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what we’re asked to do\N—listen and take in instruction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.78,0:37:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can do that when we’re \Nnot distracted by anything else. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.78,0:37:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So if everything \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.62,0:37:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,works well on an assembly day, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.78,0:37:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we know we’ve done our job.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.96,0:37:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We can remember \Nthese hard-working brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.49,0:37:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in our prayers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.50,0:37:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can do our part to help them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.10,0:37:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If possible, volunteer to assist \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.70,0:37:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,with your congregation’s \Ncleaning assignment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.97,0:37:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,at your next assembly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.97,0:37:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Or ask about the arrangement \Nfor maintaining Assembly Halls in your area. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.98,0:37:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A few are needed to take the lead, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.85,0:37:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but they need our help \Nto get the work done.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.15,0:37:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The same is true with the great amount \Nof work in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.52,0:37:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In our discussion about Jonathan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.92,0:38:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we mentioned \Nthe zealous example of our elders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.73,0:38:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the elders “leaders” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.73,0:38:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or do they “take the lead”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.93,0:38:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the difference? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.94,0:38:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Geoffrey Jackson explains \Nin this Bethel morning worship.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.51,0:38:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,While meditating on the text this morning,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.58,0:38:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I was reminded of an experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.58,0:38:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I had many years ago as a missionary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.01,0:38:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.85,0:38:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was studying with a young man\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.12,0:38:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,who was training to be a pastor\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.12,0:38:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in his church.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.82,0:38:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This man had got to the point\Nwhere he started to attend all our meetings\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.49,0:38:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,while at the same time\Nstill attending his church gatherings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.30,0:38:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The church, obviously,\Nwas very disturbed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.80,0:38:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,about the fact that he was coming\Nto the meetings of Jehovah’s Witnesses,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.07,0:38:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and their headquarters\Nsent in a missionary from overseas \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.44,0:38:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and rectify the situation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.94,0:38:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The young man told me what happened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.21,0:38:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He said the missionary asked him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.21,0:38:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“What is it that impresses you\Nabout Jehovah’s Witnesses?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.55,0:39:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “Well, one of the things is\Nthat they do the preaching work.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.09,0:39:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The missionary replied, \N“Well, our church can do that too.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.69,0:39:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the next time they had a service, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.13,0:39:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the missionary conducted the service \Nand with great zeal and enthusiasm \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.83,0:39:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,demanded that everyone in the church\Ntake part in the preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.04,0:39:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He announced the time that they\Nwould have the group to go preaching. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.04,0:39:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The young man told me \Nquite a number of people came along. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.18,0:39:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was just one thing missing,\Nyou guessed it, the missionary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.52,0:39:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt that it was enough\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.85,0:39:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just to encourage everybody else\Nto do it without engaging in it himself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.42,0:39:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How different was the example\Nof Jesus and of our hard-working elders\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.43,0:39:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,who do take the lead\Nwith regard to the preaching work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.07,0:39:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s take our Bibles\Nand turn to a very interesting scripture\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.07,0:39:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in Hebrews 13:7, 17. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.08,0:39:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I’d like to highlight the beauty\Nof the New World Translation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.25,0:40:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in these two verses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.28,0:40:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You see at the beginning of verse 7:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.62,0:40:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember those\Nwho are taking the lead among you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.99,0:40:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And then verse 17:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.99,0:40:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be obedient to those\Nwho are taking the lead among you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.69,0:40:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at other Bibles,\Nwhether new or old,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.20,0:40:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,most of them say “your leaders.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.50,0:40:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, obviously,\Nthe New World Translation Committee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.30,0:40:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,had in mind Jesus’ comments with regard\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.24,0:40:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to no one being a leader among us,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.14,0:40:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and although it’s a different\Nword in the Greek text, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.28,0:40:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,still in English we can’t help\Nbut be sensitive to that matter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.55,0:40:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this accurate translation\Nof saying “taking the lead”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.55,0:40:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,really summarizes, doesn’t it,\Nwhat the role is of an elder. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.16,0:40:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re not leaders, \Nbut we set the right example.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.06,0:40:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this accurate translation\Nis also portrayed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.70,0:40:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,in the words of our Lord Jesus Christ \Nas recorded in Luke chapter 22, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.37,0:41:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll be interested to note\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.14,0:41:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is part of the revision\Nof the New World Translation text. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.55,0:41:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke 22:26, \Nit now portrays accurately\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.48,0:41:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that both expressions in Hebrew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.99,0:41:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and this one here are the same word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.42,0:41:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Luke 22:26,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.60,0:41:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: \N“You, though, are not to be that way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.33,0:41:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But let the one who is the greatest\Namong you become as the youngest.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.77,0:41:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then notice: \N“and the one taking the lead,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.14,0:41:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,now this is the same expression\Nas in the Hebrews, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.04,0:41:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“as the one ministering.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.08,0:41:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, obviously,\Nto take the lead means to do the work,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.08,0:41:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a minister,\Nto be a servant, to serve others.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.02,0:41:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This also reminds me, \Nmany years ago,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.66,0:41:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,when I worked with the translation team\Nin the Pacific nation of Samoa. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.66,0:41:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,At that point, we were trying to select\Nan accurate expression\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.57,0:42:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,, to convey this thought of “taking the lead.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.77,0:42:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And there were two words eventually\Nthat the brothers\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.74,0:42:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,were trying to select between, \Nor choose between. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.64,0:42:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,One was the word ta’ita’i\Nand the other ta’imua. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.75,0:42:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you don’t have\Nto remember those words,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.22,0:42:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but as a foreigner,\NI didn’t really understand\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.09,0:42:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the subtleties between\Nthe difference of the two words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.99,0:42:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So I asked the brothers, \N“How can you explain to me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.62,0:42:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what these two words mean?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.79,0:42:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the brothers was very eloquent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.86,0:42:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: “Well, just imagine\Na procession, a parade. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.90,0:42:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“So a ta’ita’i is the old man who sits\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.34,0:42:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“on the side of the road\Nbarking out the orders: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.27,0:42:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘You should do it this way;\Nyou should do it that way.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.91,0:42:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“The ta’imua, on the other hand, \Nis the one right in the front of the parade\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.78,0:42:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,taking the lead\Nand everyone’s following him.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.82,0:42:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Which word do you think we selected?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.82,0:42:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn’t that summarize nicely just exactly\Nwhat’s involved with being an elder? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.83,0:43:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not a matter of sitting\Non the sidelines barking out orders\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.56,0:43:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but getting involved,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.56,0:43:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,setting the right example,\Nand then others following. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.70,0:43:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is in harmony\Nwith one Greek lexicon\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.60,0:43:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that describes\Nthis expression this way, it says, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.51,0:43:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“The concept of leading can be expressed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.48,0:43:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“by showing how to do something, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.28,0:43:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“demonstrating how we ought to do it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.68,0:43:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and going ahead showing the way.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.38,0:43:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, on the other hand,\Nsome religions even view\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.19,0:43:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression “elder” as a title. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.19,0:43:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve probably heard of them\Nintroducing themselves,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.19,0:43:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“Good morning, I’m Elder Jackson.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.10,0:43:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course,\Nnone of us would want to view\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.80,0:43:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,being an elder as a title\Nin the sense of a position\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.07,0:43:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that lords it over others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.17,0:43:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that in mind,\Nanother subtlety to the revision\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.88,0:43:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is seen in 1 Timothy chapter 3, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.71,0:43:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so please turn there with me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.55,0:43:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,1 Timothy 3:1. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.42,0:44:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,These are well-known words\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.16,0:44:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,—particularly when brothers are considering\Nthe qualifications for elders—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.16,0:44:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but you may or may not have seen\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.10,0:44:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the subtleties of the change\Nhere in this revision. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.87,0:44:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It says now:\N“This statement is trustworthy: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.44,0:44:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“If a man is reaching out to be an overseer,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.97,0:44:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,he is desirous of a fine work.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.48,0:44:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember before \Nthe original New World Translation said:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.48,0:44:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,‘If someone is reaching out \Nfor the office of being an overseer?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.36,0:44:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And that reflected\Nand no doubt was influenced\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.89,0:44:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,by the King James \Nand many of the older translations\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.56,0:44:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that translated it that way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.03,0:44:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we look at the rest of the verse, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.70,0:44:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that it’s not the office,\Nor the position, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.60,0:44:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of being an overseer\Nthat someone reaches out for;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.21,0:44:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,rather, it’s the work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.28,0:45:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the hard work that needs \Nto be done by an overseer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.85,0:45:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,An overseer recognizes\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.08,0:45:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that he needs to work hard\Nat setting the right example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.92,0:45:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then others will follow\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.92,0:45:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—rather than just telling\Neveryone what they should do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.36,0:45:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we look at these subtleties\Nin the New World Translation,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.17,0:45:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,it only helps us to appreciate\Nit even more, doesn’t it?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.17,0:45:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So with this in mind,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.97,0:45:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,what does our text this morning\Nhelp us to keep in mind? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.84,0:45:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as elders, what do we need to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.71,0:45:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Not sit on the sidelines\Nbarking out orders but, rather, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.45,0:45:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the lead,\Nbe in the forefront, do the work,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.42,0:45:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and then others will follow our example,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.86,0:45:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just as we follow the example of Jesus.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.73,0:45:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible gives us a clear understanding \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.26,0:45:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Jehovah wants us \Nto do in the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.60,0:45:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Elders take the lead by doing the work, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.54,0:45:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and we follow their good example.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.34,0:46:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Applying God’s Word \Ncontributes to our being fellow workers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.68,0:46:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,under peaceful conditions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.08,0:46:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But we could be distracted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.08,0:46:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,even when our brothers \Nand sisters are right there with us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.11,0:46:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What are these distractions? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.49,0:46:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see in this music video.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.83,0:46:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Think—think outside the box.\NBe someone who talks.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.50,0:46:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t waste away behind that tiny screen\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.61,0:46:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,’Cause you know \Nthat there’s much more to life\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.51,0:46:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Than friend requests and likes.\NThink of all the things we haven’t seen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.25,0:46:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.35,0:46:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll never see them\Nif you’re focused on the superficial.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.79,0:46:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You need real friends, \Nif you know what I mean.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.39,0:46:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.\NCan you see\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.90,0:47:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What I see?\NAround the world, this happy family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.97,0:47:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.\NDo you know\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.97,0:47:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What I know?\NThat you belong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.28,0:47:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Put down the phone, and look at me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.02,0:47:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Take—take the time to see.\NSee what others see.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.46,0:47:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t trade that plastic box\Nfor all your friends.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.96,0:47:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make friends you know are true,\NWho love Jehovah too,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.07,0:47:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’ll stand right \Nby your side until the end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.47,0:47:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.44,0:47:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll never meet them\Nif you’re focused on the superficial.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.94,0:47:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You need real friends,\Nif you know what I mean.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.75,0:47:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.\NCan you see\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.92,0:47:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What I see?\NAround the world, this happy family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.29,0:47:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.\NDo you know\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.29,0:48:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What I know?\NThat you belong.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.60,0:48:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Put down the phone, and look at me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.98,0:48:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t let it play you for a fool.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.02,0:48:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What you’re getting \Ncould be fact or could be fiction.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.73,0:48:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Life in the cloud can be so cruel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.87,0:48:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you come back down to earth,\Nconverse, and reverse the addiction?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.49,0:49:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Put—put down your device\N’Cause if you don’t think twice,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.30,0:49:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The best in life will surely pass you by.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.87,0:49:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, listen, taste, and touch—\NThe things we love so much\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.91,0:49:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Have been here all along. \NAll you need to do is\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.14,0:49:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize what’s in your hand\Nis only superficial.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.75,0:49:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve got real friends, \Nif you know what I mean.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.45,0:49:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.\NCan you see\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.76,0:49:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What I see?\NAround the world, this happy family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.06,0:49:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.\NDo you know\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.07,0:49:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What I know?\NThat you belong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.37,0:49:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Put down the phone, and look at me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.41,0:49:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see\NWhat I see?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.08,0:50:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Around the world, this happy family.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.08,0:50:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at me.\NDo you know\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.09,0:50:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What I know?\NThat you belong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.32,0:50:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Put down the phone, and look at me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.36,0:50:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Time spent with our brothers \Nand sisters is precious. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.80,0:50:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Make the most of it \Nby setting aside anything \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.07,0:50:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that could distract \Nfrom the interchange of encouragement.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.81,0:50:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, though, \Nour viewpoint of ones in the congregation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.81,0:50:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,hides their true beauty that Jehovah sees. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.65,0:50:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the sister \Nin this dramatization learn that lesson and, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.39,0:50:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in turn, \Nbecome more beautiful herself?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.41,0:51:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Miki. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.41,0:51:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I moved here one year ago. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.08,0:51:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was so nice and friendly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.36,0:51:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s how I felt in the beginning.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.55,0:51:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not your babysitter!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.36,0:51:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn’t you see we were talking?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.04,0:52:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! \NThis is not a park!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.01,0:52:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the elders are always busy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.38,0:52:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not sure if they really want me here.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.22,0:52:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoko, a pioneer sister\Nfrom my former congregation, visited me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.20,0:52:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She asked me how I was doing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.07,0:52:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I told her how I felt\Nabout my congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.24,0:52:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then she told me that she\Nhad a similar experience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.78,0:52:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And she shared with me\Na Watchtower article that helped her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.02,0:52:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I made this my next personal study project.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.56,0:52:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“What do you see when you look at others? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.53,0:53:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you have the tendency\Nto view what they say or do\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.36,0:53:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“as either black or white, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.97,0:53:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as if no other colors or shades existed?”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.10,0:53:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Having that viewpoint\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.81,0:53:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“would be like a photographer\Nwho ignores the large variety\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.91,0:53:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“of brilliant hues and shades\Nin an autumn landscape, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.55,0:53:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as if only black and white images existed.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.79,0:53:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I’ve been viewing\Nthe congregation as “black and white.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.50,0:53:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The article then turned\Nmy attention to Jesus’ example.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.33,0:53:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“The spirit, of course, is eager,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.11,0:53:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but the flesh is weak.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.34,0:53:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was Jesus able to say such kind words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.45,0:53:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to his disciples?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.49,0:54:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Insight is the ability to put yourself\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.93,0:54:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in the other’s place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.66,0:54:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus did that with his disciples. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.30,0:54:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, I need to do the same.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.04,0:54:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She always looks after the children at home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.87,0:54:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She also needs time to be refreshed\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.51,0:54:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,by association with friends\Nat the Kingdom Hall.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.51,0:54:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She probably didn’t mean to be rude. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.35,0:54:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Since we looked like we were\Nhaving an enjoyable conversation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.69,0:54:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,she may have just wanted to join us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.99,0:54:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders are so busy caring for the needs\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.76,0:54:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.23,0:54:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I know they’re doing the best they can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.83,0:54:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to do what\NI can to make their job easier.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.09,0:55:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Miki,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.53,0:55:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you are such a beautiful Christian. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.60,0:55:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so glad to have you \Nin our congregation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.34,0:55:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,“The insight of a man certainly\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.84,0:55:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“slows down his anger,\Nand it is beauty on his part\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.75,0:55:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to overlook an offense.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.69,0:55:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’d like to make this lesson a topic \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.93,0:55:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for your personal study or family worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.93,0:55:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you can review \Nthe March 15, 2008, Watchtower article \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.10,0:55:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning on page 25. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.71,0:56:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The title asks the question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.17,0:56:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do You View Others as Jehovah Does?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.92,0:56:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When we share Jehovah’s view of others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.36,0:56:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re better equipped \Nto be fellow workers with God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.43,0:56:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and with our brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.12,0:56:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, this month’s report \Nfrom fellow workers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.96,0:56:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,comes to us \Nfrom the country of Georgia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.69,0:56:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Forests, streams, and lush valleys \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.06,0:56:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,adorn this mountainous region \Non the border of Europe and Asia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.35,0:56:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Georgia’s capital, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.75,0:56:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Tbilisi, is a bustling city \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.92,0:56:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,where modern buildings \Nmix with historic architecture.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.70,0:56:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Georgian people are known \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.31,0:56:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for their strong family ties \Nand warm hospitality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.02,0:56:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Folk music and dances \Nare a rich part of their culture. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.79,0:56:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Visitors are offered to try \Na variety of delicious local foods, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.71,0:56:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,such as this candy \Nmade from walnuts and grape juice.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.73,0:56:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Old town Sighnaghi is a unique place \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.77,0:57:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy the beautiful landscape and culture. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.15,0:57:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The congregation here has 50 publishers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.66,0:57:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who keep busy in the preaching work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.63,0:57:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite being a small congregation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.33,0:57:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they represent almost 3 percent \Nof the town’s population. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.12,0:57:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Remote towns and villages \Ncreate opportunities to preach \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.04,0:57:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,in unassigned territories \Nthroughout the year.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.17,0:57:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank the congregation in Sighnaghi \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.91,0:57:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the more than 18,000 brothers \Nand sisters in Georgia \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.38,0:57:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for this encouraging visit with them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.72,0:57:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And we send them and all of you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.52,0:57:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,our warm Christian love and greetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.37,0:57:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,From the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.19,0:57:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.\N
